<HEADLINE>
FT  21 NOV 94 / Company News (This Week): Market tunes in for showing of LWT
integration - Granada
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Granada Group, the broadcasting, leisure, rental and business services
group, is expected on Wednesday to report pre-tax profits for the year to
end-September of at least Pounds 250m, up from Pounds 176m last time.
Earnings per share are forecast at around 30p, and the dividend is expected
to be 14 per cent ahead at 10p.
The second half will see the first full contribution from London Weekend
Television, of which Granada won control in February for Pounds 760m after
the first successful hostile bid in the UK television industry. The combined
group commands about 30 per cent of UK television advertising revenue.
LWT is expected to contribute about Pounds 27m towards the television
division's total operating profits of around Pounds 80m, up from a previous
Pounds 42.5m. At the interim stage LWT had been with the group for just a
month, and made a contribution of Pounds 4.7m.
Mr Gerry Robinson, chief executive, said in June that he had been 'rather
confused' by City rumours that the integration of LWT was going badly. 'In
fact, it is one of the easiest integrations we have been involved with,' he
said.
Since then the group has started integrating the non-programme making
activities of Granada Television and LWT with the loss of between 150 and
200 jobs from a combined staff of
2,000.
Despite an underlying decline in sales at the rental division, operating
profits are seen rising to around Pounds 110m, from a previous Pounds 105m.
Mobile telephones, satellite subscriptions and the sale of second-hand
equipment are expected to make good progress.
The leisure sector is forecast to contribute Pounds 46m (Pounds 37.5m),
while a sharp increase at Sutcliffe Catering is expected to help the
business services division increase operating profits to Pounds 50m (Pounds
17.4m).
</TEXT>
