<HEADLINE>
FT  21 NOV 94 / Arts (Openings): Amsterdam
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
An unusual exhibition of late medieval art opens at the Rijksmuseum on
Saturday. Entitled 'The Art of Devotion 1300-1500', it brings together 50
paintings, miniatures, goldsmiths' work and prints. Among the artists are
Mantegna and Memling. The objects - small in size and made with precious
materials - represent some of the most beautiful works of art of the period.
</TEXT>
