FT  21 NOV 94 / Arts (Openings): Paris
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
The Kirov Opera is in residence at the Theatre des Champs-Elysees for the
next three weeks, with staged performances of Tchaikovsky's 'The Queen of
Spades', Mussorgsky's 'Khovanshchina' and two Rimsky-Korsakov rarities -
'Sadko' and 'Legend of the Invisible City of Kitezh'. The casts include
