<HEADLINE>
FT  21 NOV 94 / Plea for two more London airfields
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
London's Heathrow and Gatwick airports could handle an extra 30m passengers
a year if two other small airfields were developed, the Adam Smith
Institute, the free market think-tank, said in a report yesterday.
The institute said expanding RAF Northolt in Middlesex and Redhill aerodrome
in Surrey would take much pressure off Heathrow and Gatwick. The government
is already considering developing Northolt - six miles from Heathrow and
currently used for Royal Family, VIP and military flights - for business and
smaller commercial aircraft.
