</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
September 29: VSEL announces takeover talks with unnamed party, subsequently
confirmed as BAe.
October 12: BAe launches agreed Pounds 480m offer worth about Pounds 12.60 a
share with cash alternative of Pounds 11.40.
October 18: VSEL announces 5 per cent rise in interim pre-tax profits to
Pounds 30.2m.
October 21: Takeover Panel asks GEC to clarify its intentions towards VSEL.
October 28: GEC makes Pounds 14 a share cash bid valuing VSEL at Pounds
532m.
November 18: BAe increases value of share offer to about Pounds 14.80 and
raises cash alterative to match GEC at Pounds 14.
