<HEADLINE>
FT  19 NOV 94 / Weekend Money (Financial Planning): Two incomes, two
pensions? - Briefcase, Q&amp;A
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
I work on salary for the University of London and also have freelance
consultancy income. My salary is taxed under PAYE and the consultancy
earnings under Schedule D.
I pay pension contributions from my salary to the Universities
Superannuation Scheme (USS) but make no further pension provision from the
freelance earnings. Can I remain in the USS and, simultaneously, take out a
personal pension funded solely from my freelance earnings?
There is no reason why you cannot start a personal pension based on your
freelance earnings while remaining in the occupational scheme in respect of
your salary. You might also like to consider making free-standing additional
voluntary contribution (FSAVC) payments at the same time as contributing to
a personal pension. (Reply by Murray Johnstone Personal Asset Management).
No legal responsibility can be accepted by the Financial Times for the
answers given in these columns. All inquiries will be answered by post as
soon as possible.
